<br>
Monks are in such sorry shape in game already that I wouldn't have the heart to wake him even though we could.  From what I've heard chatting with others that could, they feel pretty much the same about waking, though perhaps for different reasons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thraallfv>ThraallFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 937<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/9/03 12:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4860.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.calpoly.edu/~msamuel/frgSthrl.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I suspect the sleeper will end up ..</span><hr size=1> Agreed no reason to ever wake him.<br>
